@Blackworm\_Bloodworm: I'll downvote any person who states "... just about each block we get creatures that overshadow ", and then goes on to compare it to [Rakdos Cackler](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Rakdos Cackler) (from the ***newest*** set) while wrongly using the term "strictly better".  
First off, there haven't been a single hybrid red/green 1-drop as good as Tattermunge Maniac since Tattermunge Maniac. Comparing it to [Goblin Guide](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Goblin Guide) and the like just won't do, because this card has the advantage of being hybrid in a multicolor deck. This is especially relevant if you're running "color matters" cards ([Boartusk Liege](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Boartusk Liege) etc.).  
Secondly, [Rakdos Cackler](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Rakdos Cackler) doesn't have the same colors as Tattermunge Maniac, and therefore isn't "strictly better" - you can't play it with green mana. You want strictly better? Take [Walking Corpse](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Walking Corpse) and compare it with [Spineless Thug](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Spineless Thug) or [Scathe Zombies](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Scathe Zombies).... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)
